uced by French jeweler Chaumet, weigh 1.17 pounds, the silver medals weigh 1.16 pounds and the bronze comes in at an even pound.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9970585483263064, \"rank\": 0.002024274820495071, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"toThe Athletic\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medals\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"1.17 pounds\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medals\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"1.16 pounds\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"an even pound\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Approximately 0.04 pounds of the Eiffel Tower iron is included in each medal.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Approximately 0.04 pounds\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower iron\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"each medal\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theofficial Olympic website, the first eight athletes in each event \\\"receive a diploma, and their names are announced to the public.\\\"\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theofficial Olympic website\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"the first eight athletes\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"each event\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"a diploma\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"their names\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1245}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There does not appear to be a gift basket involved.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1299, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gift basket\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So all they get is a medal worth approximately $950according to Forbes.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.193033590893217e-15, \"text\": \"Forbes\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic glory is great, but you can not pay your bills with prestige.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic glory\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1386}, {\"ngram\": \"your bills\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"prestige\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, home countries often give medalists with monetary rewards.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"home countries\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"medalists\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1487}, {\"ngram\": \"monetary rewards\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Olympians get$37,500 for a gold medal, $22,500 for a silver medal and $15,000 for a bronze.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"U.S. Olympians\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other countries who win significantly fewer medals pay much more.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other countries\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"significantly fewer medals\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia, for example, isreportedly giving gold medalists$214,900 in 2024.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1675, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9996484650423595, \"rank\": 0.00020075350512450892, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medalists$214,900\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malaysia and Morocco will also pay out over $200,000 to anyone who comes home with gold.\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"score\": 0.999956170299479, \"rank\": 4.3769380391030856e-05, \"text\": \"Malaysia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\"}, {\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9999908921932763, \"rank\": 4.69341377315828e-06, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to that, track athletes who win gold get an extra $50,000 from World Athletics.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999826209206, \"rank\": 1.7379216829003337e-08, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"track athletes\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No matter how much you earn, you have always got a piece of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a piece\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals have been given since the first modern Olympic games in 1896 in Athens, Greece.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8695314883090911, \"rank\": 0.15004460817480236, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2089, \"end\": 2095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999529987720937, \"rank\": 0.00045581974282933395, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Medals\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"the first modern Olympic games\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theofficial Olympics website, first place was actually awarded a silver medal, an olive branch and a diploma.\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theofficial Olympics website\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"first place\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"an olive branch\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"a diploma\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second place got the only other medal which was a bronze-copper combination, a branch of laurel and a diploma.\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2309, \"end\": 2315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurel_wreath\", \"score\": 0.9999242878789466, \"rank\": 7.571785370376556e-05, \"text\": \"laurel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurel_wreath\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurel_wreath\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Second place\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the only other medal\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze-copper combination\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2295}, {\"ngram\": \"a branch\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2305}, {\"ngram\": \"a diploma\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the games were played inParis four years laterfirst place received gilt silver, which is a silver gilded with gold.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2346}, {\"ngram\": \"inParis\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"four years laterfirst place\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"gilt silver\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Gilt silver and gold have been interchangeable ever since.)\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gilt silver\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2465}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second place got regular silver and third place earned bronze.\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Second place\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2526}, {\"ngram\": \"regular silver\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"third pl